item.title: Projects
item.author: knowsuchagency@gmail.com (Stephan Fitzpatrick)
item.description: ninjadog: pug + jinja2 == ❤️ Documentation Pug template (formerly Jade) support for Python 3. fabric for project automation docopt for the command-line interface leverages the pug-cli library on npm to render pug templates through a subprocess continuous integration through travis-ci tested on multiple version of Python through the use of tox prior to release on pypi Sphinx to build and render documentation prior to deployment on GitHub Pages

item.author: knowsuchagency@gmail.com (Stephan Fitzpatrick)
item.description: When I’m not programming, I’m reading, exercising, or volunteering. I served six years in the Navy as a Chinese linguist. During that time, I transitioned from translation work, to intelligence analysis, and finally to software development. Co-Founder of PyHawaii, Hawaii’s Python User Group. I have also been involved in HiCapacity, Code for Hawaii, Code for San Francisco, and Data for Democracy. Feel free to say hello. I love meeting new people :)
